DOS-PORT (patch 0082, Phase 9 wave 17.4).

Pre-patch: the wave-15 dirty-rect path tracked drawSurface destinations
via _record_dirty_rect, but the coalesce-and-collapse step always
ended with a screen-spanning bounding box every flip (per the wave-17.1
investigation). Wave-17.3's backdrop cache made the bg one drawcall
but its dirty rect IS still full-screen. Result: dirty_path_taken=0,
full_flush_taken=100, dirty_pct_x10=1000 every block on real HW.

This patch adds a prev-frame buffer (one screen-sized SDL_Surface,
~76 KB at 320×240 INDEX8) and a per-scanline diff against current
window contents. The diff produces full-width row-band rects covering
only the actually-changed scanlines. The engine's drawcall-tracked
_dirty_rects is OVERWRITTEN with the diff result before the threshold
decision. When diff produces small dirty area (title menu's static
content with small parallax band, dialog overlays, paused gameplay),
threshold doesn't trip → SDL_UpdateWindowSurfaceRects fires with the
real partial list.

Pairs with SDL/0033 which makes DOSVESA_UpdateWindowFramebuffer's
pitches_match branches honor the rect list (the engine-side win is
moot if SDL ignores the rects).

Five changes in Renderer.h / Renderer.cpp:

1. Renderer.h: new state —  (the buffer),
    (killswitch cache), three diagnostic
   accumulators (diff_calls / diff_rects_sum / diff_dirty_pct_sum).

2. Renderer.cpp helpers —
   (env-var killswitch probe; default ON, set
   SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_PREVFRAME_DIFF=0 to disable) and
    (per-scanline memcmp returning a list
   of full-width row-band rects, coalesces contiguous dirty rows).

3. Renderer::flip(): inserted before the dirty-pixel decision —
   when diff is enabled and prev_frame_surface is valid+matching, drain
   queued slow-path renderer commands (so the window surface reflects
   all engine drawcalls), then run the diff and OVERWRITE _dirty_rects.
   The existing threshold + first_n_force + force_full_refresh checks
   gate the partial-flush dispatch as before — the diff just changes
   the input.

4. Renderer::flip(): post-flush — lazy alloc / re-alloc / blit current
   window → prev_frame_surface so next flip's diff has the right
   reference. Skipped when diff is disabled (saves ~0.5 ms / flip).

5. Renderer::flushAll() / Renderer::~Renderer(): release
   prev_frame_surface so the next flip recomputes it from scratch
   (resource reload / scene reset / mode change).

The per-100-flip diagnostic block now emits a sibling line:

showing the actual dirty area % discovered by the diff. On title screen
this should be ~30-40% (parallax + cursor) vs the dirty-rect-block's
constant 100% from the drawcall coalesce.

Memory cost: ~76 KB heap on Tier 1 (PODP83 + 48 MB).
CPU cost: 240 SDL_memcmp(320 bytes) + one 76 KB SDL_BlitSurface per
flip ≈ 1-2 ms. Win: every byte not flushed to VRAM saves ~3.5 us at
the measured Mach64 PCI write throughput. Title screen with ~70%
static area should save ~35-50 KB / flush × 3.5 us = ~12-17 ms / flush.
Honest variance per memory perf_predictions_unreliable.md is wide;
real-HW measures.
